content: I've been searching for the 1943 copper cent, but it's definitely out of my budget. I've been focusing on more affordable error coins, like the 1972 Doubled Die Obverse Lincoln cent. I've also been trying to learn more about the history of coin collecting, which is how I got started with collecting in the first place. Speaking of which, I've been collecting for about two months now, and it's been a really rewarding hobby so far.
